{
  "stem": "3012.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, because they-- they-- the Russians came, and one or two people opened the storage area, and then they sort of disappeared.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they probably went through town, liberating-- there were a number of small camps in the-- in the vicinity.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I don't remember ever having seen-- I-- I-- I saw Belgian prisoners walking around town, but I-- I don't remember ever talking to Russians.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, I don't speak Russian, so I wouldn't-- couldn't be sort of a help myself.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we wanted to come back to-- to Hungary, but we had to get organized, and we had to catch our breath and all that.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then a Red Cross unit from New Zealand came to camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were looking for people they wanted to have as their interpreter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I volunteered.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But-- but I was so weak and-- and so terribly emaciated myself, that I couldn't keep up with them except for a few days.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they also told us that they could make it-- they could-- they could facilitate our journey should we decide to go to New Zealand.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then we thanked them profusely, but told them that we want to be reunited with the family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, a Red Cross unit from New Zealand.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And whether they did not want to tell us the truth about Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because probably by-- by middle of May, the Allied had a good idea what happened in the East, I'm sure, and in the West, and in all the camps.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we-- we were not apprised.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So finally, we set out to go back to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
